// tb_accuracy.cpp — Fixed Testbench
// ===================================
// BUG 1 FIX: Calls rf_top(features, /*reset=*/1) before EACH test sample.
//   This flushes the temporal sliding window so state from sample N-1
//   cannot contaminate sample N.  The reset output is discarded.
//
// BUG 2 NOTE: This testbench uses the first 300 samples from the ARFF.
//   To reach 90%+ accuracy you MUST regenerate trees.cpp using the
//   Python workflow described below — see WORKFLOW comment.
//
// ── HOW TO REACH 90%+ ACCURACY ───────────────────────────────────────────
// WORKFLOW (run on your host machine, NOT in Vivado):
//
//   Step 1 — Stratified split (run once):
//     python retrain_on_split.py \
//       --arff "EEG Eye State.arff" \
//       --test_csv test_300.csv \
//       --forest_json forest_split.json
//
//   Step 2 — Generate HLS trees:
//     python json_to_trees.py \
//       --json forest_split.json \
//       --out_dir D:/IP/files/
//
//   Step 3 — Replace tb_accuracy.cpp samples with test_300.csv contents
//     (use the companion script: python csv_to_tb.py --csv test_300.csv)
//
//   Step 4 — Re-run C Simulation in Vivado HLS (synthesis is already done)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

